import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='location', y='precipitation', data=data)
    ax.set(xlabel='Location', ylabel='Precipitation')
    ax.xaxis.label.set_rotation(0)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation in Seattle and New York?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data = data[data['location'] == 'Seattle']

    ax.set(xlabel='Date', ylabel='Maximum Temperature')
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('How does the maximum temperature vary over time in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    data['day'] = data['date'].dt.day
    data['weekday'] = data['date'].dt.weekday_name
    data = data.drop(['date'], axis=1)
    data = data.groupby(['location', 'weather']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    chart = sns.barplot(x='weather', y='counts', hue='location', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the most common type of weather in Seattle and New York?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
